name: tumpak sewu waterfall
description:
Tumpak Sewu, also known as Coban Sewu, is a tiered waterfall located between Pronojiwo District, Lumajang District, and Ampelgading District, Malang Regency, in East Java, Indonesia. This waterfall is one of the cold lava trails from Mount Semeru, an active volcano and the highest mountain in Java. The Glidik River that flows in Semeru is the main water source for the waterfall.

Total height	120 metres (390 ft)
